add_logo functions

add_logo <- function(plot_path, logo_path, logo_position, logo_scale = 10){
  # Requires magick R Package https://github.com/ropensci/magick
  # Useful error message for logo position
  if (!logo_position %in% c("top right", "top left", "bottom right", "bottom left")) {
    stop("Error Message: Uh oh! Logo Position not recognized\n  Try: logo_positon = 'top left', 'top right', 'bottom left', or 'bottom right'")
  }
  # read in raw images
  plot <- magick::image_read(plot_path)
  logo_raw <- magick::image_read(logo_path)
  # get dimensions of plot for scaling
  plot_height <- magick::image_info(plot)$height
  plot_width <- magick::image_info(plot)$width
  # default scale to 1/10th width of plot
  # Can change with logo_scale
  logo <- magick::image_scale(logo_raw, as.character(plot_width/logo_scale))
  # Get width of logo
  logo_width <- magick::image_info(logo)$width
  logo_height <- magick::image_info(logo)$height
  # Set position of logo
  # Position starts at 0,0 at top left
  # Using 0.01 for 1% - aesthetic padding
  if (logo_position == "top right") {
    x_pos = plot_width - logo_width - 0.01 * plot_width
    y_pos = 0.01 * plot_height
  } else if (logo_position == "top left") {
    x_pos = 0.01 * plot_width
    y_pos = 0.01 * plot_height
  } else if (logo_position == "bottom right") {
    x_pos = plot_width - logo_width - 0.01 * plot_width
    y_pos = plot_height - logo_height - 0.01 * plot_height
  } else if (logo_position == "bottom left") {
    x_pos = 0.01 * plot_width
    y_pos = plot_height - logo_height - 0.01 * plot_height
  }
  # Compose the actual overlay
  magick::image_composite(plot, logo, offset = paste0("+", x_pos, "+", y_pos))
}

Clean LAFC

# place each vector into list
resultados <- list(PlayerNames, age, minutes)

col_name <- c("name", "age", "minutes")

results_comb <- resultados %>% 
  reduce(cbind) %>% 
  as_tibble() %>%
  set_names(col_name)
## Warning: The `x` argument of `as_tibble.matrix()` must have unique column names if `.name_repair` is omitted as of tibble 2.0.0.
## Using compatibility `.name_repair`.
## join + bday
resultados2 <- list(PlayerNames2, bday, 
                    joinedteam, leaveteam)

col_name2 <- c("name", "bday", "join", "leave")

results_comb2 <- resultados2 %>% 
  reduce(cbind) %>% 
  as_tibble() %>%
  set_names(col_name2)

## combine BOTH
lafc_comb <- results_comb %>%
  left_join(results_comb2, by="name")

# fix "strings" into proper formats, calculate % of minutes appeared
lafc <- lafc_comb %>%
  mutate(age = as.numeric(age),
         minutes = minutes %>%
           str_replace_all(c("\\." = "","'"="")) %>%
           as.numeric(),
         minutes_perc = (minutes / 3060) %>%
           round(digits = 3),
         bday = bday %>%
           str_replace("\\(.*\\)","") %>%
           mdy(),
         join = join %>% mdy(),
         join_age = case_when(
           name == "Cristian Arango" ~ 26.2,
           name == "Jamal Blackman" ~ 27.8,
           name == "Sebastien Ibeagha" ~ 19.4,
           name == "Danny Crisostomo" ~ 24.4,
           name == "Michee Ngalina" ~ 21.3,
           TRUE ~ interval(bday, join) / years(1)),
         age_now = case_when(
           TRUE ~ interval(bday, Sys.Date()) / years(1)),
         duration = age_now - join_age) %>%
  filter(!is.na(minutes)) %>%
  separate(name, into = c("first_name", "last_name"), 
           sep = " ", fill = "left") %>%
  mutate(fname = if_else(!is.na(first_name), 
                  str_extract(first_name, "[A-Z]{1}"),
                  ""),
         player = case_when(
           !is.na(first_name) ~ glue("{fname}. {last_name}"),
           TRUE ~ last_name),
         team_name = "LAFC") %>%
  arrange(desc(minutes_perc))

Peak Age

# rectanglular highlight for players in their prime:
rect_df <- data.frame(
  xmin = 25, xmax = 29,
  ymin = -Inf, ymax = Inf
)

lafc_plot <- lafc %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x = age_now, y = minutes_perc)) +
    geom_vline(xintercept = 25, alpha = 0.4, color = "grey20") +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0.5, alpha = 0.4, color = "grey20") +
    geom_rect(data = rect_df,
              aes(x = NULL, y = NULL,
                  xmin = xmin, xmax = xmax,
                  ymin = ymin, ymax = ymax),
              fill = "#c39e6d", alpha = 0.7) +
    geom_link(aes(x = join_age, xend = age_now,
                  y = minutes_perc, yend = minutes_perc,
                  alpha = stat(index)), 
              color = "#000000", size = 1.5) + 
    geom_point(aes(x = age_now), color = "#e31837", size = 3.5) +
    geom_text_repel(
      aes(label = player),
      nudge_y = 0.01,
      seed = 6) + 
    annotate("text", x = 27, y = 1.055,
             size = 5.5, fontface = "bold",
             family = "Rockwell",
             label = "Peak Years", color = "grey20") +
    scale_y_continuous(
      expand = c(0.01, 0),
      limits = c(0, 1.08), 
      breaks = seq(0, 1, by = 0.2), 
      labels = percent_format()) +
    scale_x_continuous(
      limits = c(17, 33),
      breaks = seq(18, 34, by = 2)) +
    labs(
      x = "Age", 
      y = "Minutes Played (%)",  
      title = "<span style = 'color: #c39e6d' > Los Angeles Football Club </span> | Squad Age Profile",
      subtitle = "Major League Soccer 2021 (100% = 3060 total Minutes)") +
    theme_bw() +
    theme(
      text = element_text(family = "Rockwell"),
      plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#000000"),
      panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white"),
      panel.border = element_blank(),
      plot.title = element_markdown(color = "white", size = 20, face = "bold"),
      plot.subtitle = element_text(color = "white", size = 18),
      plot.caption = element_text(size = 14),
      panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
      axis.text.x = element_text(color = "white"),
      axis.title.y = element_text(color = "white", vjust= 0.5),
      axis.title = element_text(color = "white", size = 16),
      axis.text = element_text(color = "white", size = 14),
      axis.ticks = element_blank(),
      legend.position = "none")
